title.label: Can't Go Wrong with This One

content.label:
Business has been slow, and due to that, one of the first thing I have to cut back on is spending money on apps. So I've been on the hunt for some free ones. As many of us know, most of the time the free ones are just a vehicle to nickel and dime you out of more cash than you would spend on a paid app. Not this game. I have found hours of fun in this well thought out, challenging, and addictive game. Bolstered by its beautiful graphics, and it's rotating side challenges, you can't go wrong with this game.

If there is one complaint I have, it's that some of the challenges are a bit ambiguous, but not worth taking a star rating away, because there's some chance that's on me.
A really good, well rounded game that provides hoursof fun

First off, I have an iPhone 4s, and have no technical problems at all with this game, so I don't know what some of the other reviews are talking about.  The controls are perfect, you can choose between touch or tilt controls which is a nice plus.  There's sixty standard levels across six really well done themes, ranging from City to China to a Tiki Paradise.  There's ten unlockable bonus levels.  There's ten gift levels where you can unlock new frisbees etc.  Money earned in the game can be spent on unlocking levels or buying different frisbees.  The different music tracks match the theme of the corresponding level very well.  The graphics are surprisingly great.  There's tons of replay value to get a bronze, silver, or gold medal in each level.  There are bonuses for achievements.  The stage designs are exceptionally well done.  I've spent hours on this game and can't say enough good things about it!  Masterfully done!  Download it now!
